The paper deals with the problem of 1-bit quantized precoding in multiuser MIMO systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of branch and bound is a common optimization technique in computer science, which could place the paper under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm, which could also make it relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
